00:07:49.149 --> 00:07:54.920
Now I want to open both and
ask, what will I get?

00:07:54.920 --> 00:07:58.023
In Newtonian mechanics,
there's only one possible

00:07:58.023 --> 00:08:00.545
answer to that question,
and that is 10,

00:08:00.545 --> 00:08:04.360
because we've got 5 this way
and you've got 5 that way.

00:08:04.360 --> 00:08:06.684
And you open both,
whoever is going this way will

00:08:06.684 --> 00:08:09.137
keep going that way;
whoever is going this way will

00:08:09.137 --> 00:08:10.110
keep going this way.
 

00:08:10.110 --> 00:08:13.519
They will add up to give you 10.
 

00:08:13.519 --> 00:08:14.730
Now I told you,
some people may say,

00:08:14.730 --> 00:08:17.293
"Well, maybe it's not 10,
because with both slits open,

00:08:17.293 --> 00:08:20.079
maybe someone from here can
collide with someone from there.

00:08:20.079 --> 00:08:21.709
How do you know that will not
happen?"

00:08:21.709 --> 00:08:24.290
So I'm saying,
do the experiment with such a

00:08:24.290 --> 00:08:27.589
feeble beam of electrons,
there's only one electron at a

00:08:27.589 --> 00:08:29.149
time in the whole lab.
 

00:08:29.149 --> 00:08:31.100
It's not going to collide with
itself.

00:08:31.100 --> 00:08:35.960
Then you wait long enough,
and you have to get 5 5 = 10.

00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:40.062
And what I'm telling you is
that if you go to the location

00:08:40.062 --> 00:08:43.230
marked x,
where you've got 5 with each

00:08:43.230 --> 00:08:46.759
one open, when you open both,
you will get 0.

00:08:46.759 --> 00:08:49.440
You don't get anything.
 

00:08:49.440 --> 00:08:51.230
That is a great mystery.
 

00:08:51.230 --> 00:08:53.139
That is the end of Newtonian
physics.

00:08:53.139 --> 00:08:56.904
And I told you that something
like that never happens in your

00:08:56.904 --> 00:08:57.720
daily life.
 

00:08:57.720 --> 00:09:00.070
I gave an example with machine
guns.

00:09:00.070 --> 00:09:01.080
This is a machine gun.
 

00:09:01.080 --> 00:09:05.777
This is a concrete wall with 2
holes in it, and there's some

00:09:05.777 --> 00:09:07.288
target here, you.
 

00:09:07.288 --> 00:09:10.289
And then you see how many are
coming through this and how many

00:09:10.289 --> 00:09:11.570
are coming through that.
 

00:09:11.570 --> 00:09:13.429
Then you go there and you wait.
 

00:09:13.429 --> 00:09:15.120
And both are open.
 

00:09:15.120 --> 00:09:18.678
Somehow, nothing comes.
 

00:09:18.678 --> 00:09:21.509
With the second hole in the
wall, you are safe.

00:09:21.509 --> 00:09:23.600
With one hole in the wall,
you're not safe.

00:09:23.600 --> 00:09:25.778
That can never happen with
bullets.

00:09:25.778 --> 00:09:29.820
So these electrons are not
following any path,

00:09:29.820 --> 00:09:32.239
because the minute you commit
yourself to saying it follows

00:09:32.239 --> 00:09:34.240
one path,
either through this one or

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:37.820
that, you cannot avoid the fact
that with both of them open,

00:09:37.820 --> 00:09:40.610
the intensity with 1 2 has to =
I_1

00:09:40.610 --> 00:09:41.870
I_2.
 

00:09:41.870 --> 00:09:44.480
That's the Newtonian prediction.
 

00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:48.373
And I_1
I_2 gives you 5

00:09:48.373 --> 00:09:50.320
