00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:53.394
In other places,
instead of 10,

00:09:53.394 --> 00:09:55.240
you will get 20.
 

00:09:55.240 --> 00:09:59.014
Some places you get more,
but more dramatic thing is

00:09:59.014 --> 00:10:02.269
where you get less,
where you get nothing.

00:10:02.269 --> 00:10:05.200
Therefore you abandon the
notion that electrons have any

00:10:05.200 --> 00:10:06.000
trajectories.
 

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:08.480
You don't want to abandon it,
but you have to,

00:10:08.480 --> 00:10:11.179
because that assumption,
which is very reasonable,

00:10:11.179 --> 00:10:13.330
just doesn't agree with
experiment.

00:10:13.330 --> 00:10:14.789
Then you say,
"Okay, what should I do?

00:10:14.789 --> 00:10:16.649
Newtonian mechanics is wrong.
 

00:10:16.649 --> 00:10:19.759
What's going to take its
place?"

00:10:19.759 --> 00:10:22.230
To find that,
you have to move away from this

00:10:22.230 --> 00:10:25.543
x and move up and down
this row here and see what you

00:10:25.543 --> 00:10:28.070
get, and I think I told you what
you get.

00:10:28.070 --> 00:10:32.480
You get a pattern that looks
like this.

00:10:32.480 --> 00:10:37.373
So the real I1 2 looks like
