front of it.

00:32:33.848 --> 00:32:35.890
That's a very important thing
to know.

00:32:35.890 --> 00:32:38.655
This is called a plane wave,
and a plane wave with a

00:32:38.655 --> 00:32:41.800
p right where it is
describes a particle of momentum

00:32:41.800 --> 00:32:43.700
p in particle mechanics.
 

00:32:43.700 --> 00:32:46.531
And I told you particles of
momentum p are

00:32:46.531 --> 00:32:47.298
everywhere.
 

00:32:47.298 --> 00:32:49.910
Every machine produces them,
every accelerator produces

00:32:49.910 --> 00:32:52.230
them, and if you want to
describe them in quantum

00:32:52.230 --> 00:32:54.548
mechanics, you have to know
complex numbers.

00:32:54.548 --> 00:32:57.633
There's just no way you can get
a real answer to our

00:32:57.633 --> 00:32:58.480
