00:53:56.119 --> 00:54:00.166
People are asking the following
question: how small an object

00:54:00.166 --> 00:54:04.550
has to be before I can see its
quantum mechanical fluctuations?

00:54:04.550 --> 00:54:06.653
We know that if it's like an
electron, it's completely

00:54:06.653 --> 00:54:07.210
fluctuating.
 

00:54:07.210 --> 00:54:09.079
You don't know anything.
 

00:54:09.079 --> 00:54:11.440
If it's like a bowling ball,
it seems to have a well defined

00:54:11.440 --> 00:54:11.880
position.
 

00:54:11.880 --> 00:54:14.289
Make the objects smaller and
smaller and smaller.

00:54:14.289 --> 00:54:19.530
How small can it be before it's
first beginning to show quantum

00:54:19.530 --> 00:54:23.253
effects,
like quantization of energy or

00:54:23.253 --> 00:54:27.947
quantization of momentum,
depending on the problem,

00:54:27.947 --> 00:54:31.170
or quantum fluctuations in
position?

00:54:31.170 --> 00:54:33.650
So those measurements are now
being carried out at Yale.

00:54:33.650 --> 00:54:36.766
It's a very exciting time and
it's so many years after the

00:54:36.766 --> 00:54:38.570
discovery of quantum mechanics.
 

00:54:38.570 --> 00:54:41.501
Because we knew the really big
world and we knew the really

00:54:41.501 --> 00:54:43.389
small world,
but now we're trying to go,

00:54:43.389 --> 00:54:47.043
because of nanotechnology,
continuously from big to that

00:54:47.043 --> 00:54:49.349
small,
and how small is small?

00:54:49.349 --> 00:54:50.619
That's the question?
 

00:54:50.619 --> 00:54:55.690
Can a little macroscopic object
simultaneously be in two places?

00:54:55.690 --> 00:54:57.849
Most of them seem to have a
well defined location.

00:54:57.849 --> 00:55:02.306
Can you create a situation when
it's capable of being found here

00:55:02.306 --> 00:55:03.579
and found there?
 

00:55:03.579 --> 00:55:05.626
It's very hard,
because you have to isolate the

00:55:05.626 --> 00:55:07.139
particle from the outside world.
 

00:55:07.139 --> 00:55:08.480
That's the first condition.
 

00:55:08.480 --> 00:55:10.639
That's what ruins everything.
 

00:55:10.639 --> 00:55:12.809
A quantum computer,
you must know,

00:55:12.809 --> 00:55:16.766
has got these bits called qbits
and unlike the bits in your

00:55:16.766 --> 00:55:19.324
laptop,
which are either 0 or 1,

00:55:19.324 --> 00:55:21.980
a qbit can also give you 0 or
1,

00:55:21.980 --> 00:55:26.809
but it can also be in a state
where it can give either 0 or 1

00:55:26.809 --> 00:55:28.340
on a given trial.
 

00:55:28.340 --> 00:55:32.032
The bits in your computer,
the particular bit right now is

00:55:32.032 --> 00:55:33.329
either a 0 or a 1.
 

00:55:33.329 --> 00:55:35.617
Maybe you don't know it,
but it can only give you that

00:55:35.617 --> 00:55:37.130
answer because that's what it
is.

00:55:37.130 --> 00:55:39.945
Because that bit is in contact
with the world and the world is

00:55:39.945 --> 00:55:41.469
constantly measuring its value.
 

00:55:41.469 --> 00:55:45.085
A qbit is a quantum system
which can do one of two things,

00:55:45.085 --> 00:55:48.320
but it's isolated and it's
neither this nor that.

00:55:48.320 --> 00:55:51.170
It's like the electron going
through both slits.

00:55:51.170 --> 00:55:55.909
So a quantum bit can explore
many possibilities.

00:55:55.909 --> 00:56:02.858
If you build a computer with 10
qbits it can be doing 2^(10)

00:56:02.858 --> 00:56:05.920
things at the same time.
 

00:56:05.920 --> 00:56:09.460
And if it's got a million bits,
it's 2^(million) operations,

00:56:09.460 --> 00:56:12.219
things it can be exploring at
the same time.

00:56:12.219 --> 00:56:15.954
That's why, as you know,
one of the ways to securely

00:56:15.954 --> 00:56:19.836
send your credit card
information is to use very large

00:56:19.836 --> 00:56:22.920
numbers,
on the assumption that no one

00:56:22.920 --> 00:56:24.389
can factorize them.
 

00:56:24.389 --> 00:56:27.423
You can always multiply a 100
digit number by a 100 digit

00:56:27.423 --> 00:56:29.699
number on your computer
instantaneously.

00:56:29.699 --> 00:56:32.806
But if I gave you the 200 digit
number and told you to find the

00:56:32.806 --> 00:56:34.409
two factors you won't find it.
 

00:56:34.409 --> 00:56:37.760
You won't find it in the age of
the universe.

00:56:37.760 --> 00:56:39.860
It's amazing,
but that simple problem of

00:56:39.860 --> 00:56:43.469
factorization cannot be done if
the numbers are 100 digits long,

00:56:43.469 --> 00:56:46.291
and that's the reason why
people openly broadcast the

00:56:46.291 --> 00:56:48.182
product,
they may broadcast one of the

00:56:48.182 --> 00:56:51.103
numbers,
and only the other person knows

00:56:51.103 --> 00:56:52.619
the second number.
 

00:56:52.619 --> 00:56:56.989
Now there is something somebody
called Shore,

00:56:56.989 --> 00:56:58.677
Peter Shore,
showed that if you have a

00:56:58.677 --> 00:57:01.302
quantum computer,
made up of these qbits,

00:57:01.302 --> 00:57:05.550
it can actually factor the
number exponentially faster,

00:57:05.550 --> 00:57:07.719
namely, instead of taking
10^(10 )seconds,

00:57:07.719 --> 00:57:10.760
it will take 10 seconds.
 

00:57:10.760 --> 00:57:14.650
So if you build a quantum
computer, you have two options.

00:57:14.650 --> 00:57:18.630
Either you can become famous,
or get tenure at Yale,

00:57:18.630 --> 00:57:22.434
maybe, or you can go on the
biggest shopping spree of your

00:57:22.434 --> 00:57:25.177
life,
because you can get anybody's

00:57:25.177 --> 00:57:26.699
credit card number.
 

00:57:26.699 --> 00:57:27.789
So that's the choice.
 

00:57:27.789 --> 00:57:30.458
When you come to that fork,
you decide which way you want

00:57:30.458 --> 00:57:30.840
to go.
 

00:57:30.840 --> 00:57:33.130
Maybe you can go through both
choices, I don't know.

00:57:33.130 --> 00:57:35.889
That's something in your future.
 

00:57:35.889 --> 00:57:38.030
So why is it so hard to build a
quantum computer?

00:57:38.030 --> 00:57:40.280
There are many,
many quantum systems which can

00:57:40.280 --> 00:57:42.380
do one or two things,
and can be the state,

00:57:42.380 --> 00:57:44.179
but they are both this and
that.

00:57:44.179 --> 00:57:47.579
The problem is,
they cannot be in contact with

00:57:47.579 --> 00:57:50.980
the outside world,
because single contact with

00:57:50.980 --> 00:57:52.869
them is like a dream.
 

00:57:52.869 --> 00:57:54.050
Think about it, it's gone.
 

00:57:54.050 --> 00:57:54.550
Same thing.
 

00:57:54.550 --> 00:57:56.309
Any measurement destroys it.
 

00:57:56.309 --> 00:57:59.795
Any unintended measurement also
destroys it, so you've got to

00:57:59.795 --> 00:58:01.768
keep your system fully isolated.
 

00:58:01.768 --> 00:58:04.693
A system that is not talking to
the outside world,

00:58:04.693 --> 00:58:07.320
unfortunately,
is also not talking to you.

00:58:07.320 --> 00:58:09.849
So you cannot ask it any
questions, and if it knows the

00:58:09.849 --> 00:58:11.210
answer, it cannot tell you.
 

00:58:11.210 --> 00:58:12.909
So sometimes you want it to
talk.

00:58:12.909 --> 00:58:13.860
It's like relationships.
 

00:58:13.860 --> 00:58:15.889
Sometimes you don't want it to
talk.

00:58:15.889 --> 00:58:17.070
So what do you do?
 

00:58:17.070 --> 00:58:19.362
You've got to build a system
where sometimes,

00:58:19.362 --> 00:58:21.967
in a controlled way,
you can make contact with your

00:58:21.967 --> 00:58:24.000
system, namely give it the
problem.

00:58:24.000 --> 00:58:26.556
Then it does its quantum thing,
then you've got to make a

00:58:26.556 --> 00:58:28.610
measurement to find out what the
answer is.

00:58:28.610 --> 00:58:31.550
Then you want to be able to get
into it again.

00:58:31.550 --> 00:58:35.019
So the challenge for quantum
computers is how to keep them

00:58:35.019 --> 00:58:37.760
isolated long enough to do the
calculation.

00:58:37.760 --> 00:58:40.257
That's a challenge,
how to keep it from--how to

00:58:40.257 --> 00:58:43.079
keep it in what's called a
quantum coherent state.

00:58:43.079 --> 00:58:46.880
A coherent state is really when
it's doing many things at the

00:58:46.880 --> 00:58:47.639
same time.
 

00:58:47.639 --> 00:58:52.163
All right, so I want to tell
you now more formally how to do

00:58:52.163 --> 00:58:54.079
more quantum mechanics.
 

00:58:54.079 --> 00:58:58.309
So let's take a simple example,
a particle living on a line.

00:58:58.309 --> 00:59:03.260
That's the function Y(x).
 

00:59:03.260 --> 00:59:07.244
Let's ask the following
question: how do we do business

00:59:07.244 --> 00:59:09.090
in Newtonian mechanics?
 

00:59:09.090 --> 00:59:10.309
We say, "Here's a particle.
 

00:59:10.309 --> 00:59:11.010
That's its x.
 

00:59:11.010 --> 00:59:11.679
Here's the momentum.
 

00:59:11.679 --> 00:59:13.300
That's its p."
 

00:59:13.300 --> 00:59:16.750
Given that, I know everything I
need to know right now.

00:59:16.750 --> 00:59:19.193
Angular momentum,
r x

00:59:19.193 --> 00:59:21.619
p, Kinetic energy,
p^(2)/2m.

00:59:21.619 --> 00:59:25.210
Everything is given in terms of
the coordinates and momentum.

00:59:25.210 --> 00:59:28.757
In quantum theory,
you don't even tell me where it

00:59:28.757 --> 00:59:29.119
is.
 

00:59:29.119 --> 00:59:32.786
For every possible x,
there is a function whose

00:59:32.786 --> 00:59:36.728
square, if you now square this
guy, everything will be now

00:59:36.728 --> 00:59:38.320
positive, definite.
 

00:59:38.320 --> 00:59:39.869
I don't know,
it's something like this.

00:59:39.869 --> 00:59:42.989
This is Y^(2).
 

00:59:42.989 --> 00:59:46.902
We say the height is
proportional to finding it

00:59:46.902 --> 00:59:48.010
everywhere.
 

00:59:48.010 --> 00:59:49.869
What is the condition on the
function side?

00:59:49.869 --> 00:59:52.670
The answer is,
whatever you like.

00:59:52.670 --> 00:59:56.257
Anything I can draw,
with no special effort,

00:59:56.257 --> 00:59:59.679
is a possible function for an
electron.

00:59:59.679 --> 01:00:00.780
There are no restrictions.
 

01:00:00.780 --> 01:00:03.358
It's like saying,
what should the position of the

01:00:03.358 --> 01:00:04.110
particle be?
 

01:00:04.110 --> 01:00:05.000
x.
 

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:08.510
Any x you want is a
possible x.

01:00:08.510 --> 01:00:12.768
Likewise, any Y you draw is a
possible Y.

01:00:12.768 --> 01:00:15.976
That's a set of all possible
ampli--it's called wave

01:00:15.976 --> 01:00:19.057
functions--whose square is the
set of all possible

01:00:19.057 --> 01:00:20.190
probabilities.
 

01:00:20.190 --> 01:00:24.302
So I said Y^(2),
Y at the point x^(2),

01:00:24.302 --> 01:00:29.139
is connected to the probability
of finding it at x.

01:00:29.139 --> 01:00:32.059
That has to be in fact to be
refined.

01:00:32.059 --> 01:00:33.639
That's not precisely the story.
 

01:00:33.639 --> 01:00:35.369
I'll tell you why.
 

01:00:35.369 --> 01:00:41.320
If a statistical event has got
6 possible answers,

01:00:41.320 --> 01:00:43.994
like you throw the die,
you want to get any number from

01:00:43.994 --> 01:00:46.083
1 to 6,
you can give the probability

01:00:46.083 --> 01:00:52.050
for 1,
probability for 2,3, 4,5 and 6.

01:00:52.050 --> 01:00:57.510
These are all the odds for
getting any number from 1 to 6.

01:00:57.510 --> 01:00:59.762
Since there are only a finite
number of things that can

01:00:59.762 --> 01:01:02.050
happen,
I call them I = 1 to 6,

01:01:02.050 --> 01:01:04.900
there's a probability for each
I,

01:01:04.900 --> 01:01:07.460
and if you add all the
probabilities,

01:01:07.460 --> 01:01:13.429
you should get 1.
 

01:01:13.429 --> 01:01:17.231
But if the set of things that
can happen is a continuous

01:01:17.231 --> 01:01:19.786
variable like x,
in other words,

01:01:19.786 --> 01:01:22.969
the location of the electron is
not a discrete set of numbers.

01:01:22.969 --> 01:01:26.190
It's any real number is a
possible location.

01:01:26.190 --> 01:01:29.755
Then you cannot give a finite
probability for any one

01:01:29.755 --> 01:01:30.510
x.
 

01:01:30.510 --> 01:01:33.601
If that was finite,
since the number of points is

01:01:33.601 --> 01:01:36.949
infinite, you cannot make the
total probability 1.

01:01:36.949 --> 01:01:39.311
So what we really mean by
Y^(2) is called

01:01:39.311 --> 01:01:40.449
the probability density.
 

01:01:40.449 --> 01:01:42.677
That means draw the
Y^(2),

01:01:42.677 --> 01:01:45.420
let this be the height of
Y^(2).

01:01:45.420 --> 01:01:48.760
Take a little sliver of width
dx.

01:01:48.760 --> 01:01:53.157
The area under the graph,
P(x) dx,

01:01:53.157 --> 01:01:58.324
that is the probability of
finding the electron,

01:01:58.324 --> 01:02:03.380
or whatever particle,
between x and x

01:02:03.380 --> 01:02:04.809
dx.
 

01:02:04.809 --> 01:02:05.250
You understand?
 

01:02:05.250 --> 01:02:07.309
It's called a density.
 

01:02:07.309 --> 01:02:10.300
So you don't give a finite
probability to each point.

01:02:10.300 --> 01:02:14.913
For an infinitesimal region,
you give it infinitesimal

01:02:14.913 --> 01:02:19.440
probability, which is the
function P(x) dx.

01:02:19.440 --> 01:02:23.150
And the statement that the
particle has to be somewhere,

01:02:23.150 --> 01:02:25.800
namely, all the probabilities
add up to 0,

01:02:25.800 --> 01:02:30.969
is the statement that when you
integrate this probability

01:02:30.969 --> 01:02:38.380
density from - to infinity,
namely, Y^(2)dx,

01:02:38.380 --> 01:02:50.099
from - to infinity,
that should be 1.

01:02:50.099 --> 01:02:51.820
This is called normalization.
 

01:02:51.820 --> 01:02:53.119
It's a mathematical term.
 

